node.text:
“I ride because I feel like not enough people take risks and they’re scared of things. I do it because I love it. It’s like therapy.” - @mz.pietz

Built to satisfy even the most performance-hungry appetites, the 2021 Fat Bob 114 does not disappoint. It’s a street eater with an extra helping of torque.

node.text:
Introducing the H-D X Jason Momoa Collection. Our iconic patterns and designs merge with @prideofgypsies Aloha spirit, creating a colorful collection that celebrates his love for the open road. Every piece tells a different story. All-American made. Shop now at the link in our bio.

@da_bray @ontheroam @boazkroon

node.text:
Everyone involved in the process of creating the Sportster S has an emotional connection to the bike. Today we hear from some of the folks who build it — the talented men and women at the Harley-Davidson Powertrain Operations in Menomonee Falls, WI. 

Watch the full 2021 Sportster S reveal at the link in our bio.

node.text:
In Episode 6 of Battle of the Baggers, we catch up with H-D Screamin’ Eagle factory racing team rider @KyleWyman as he revisits his @MotoAmerica #KingoftheBaggers win at @RoadAmerica and the challenges to remain on top of the podium heading into the next race this weekend at @WeatherTechRaceway.

#MotoAmerica #HarleyDavidson

node.text:
The Harley-Davidson Screamin’ Eagle factory racing team put a dominating stamp on the second round of @MotoAmerica’s #KingoftheBaggers road racing series at @RoadAmerica.
 
Watch our recap as @KyleWyman set pole position, posted the quickest lap of the race, led every lap, and took the win by more than 15 seconds. His new teammate and brother @twyman_10 finished second & @Hayden69Gillim took third to complete the podium sweep for #HarleyDavidson racers.
#MotoAmerica #RoadAmerica

node.title: Battle of the Baggers: Season 2, Episode 5

node.text:
Congrats to #HarleyDavidson Screamin’ Eagle Factory riders @kylewyman & @twyman_10 on a 1st & 2nd place finish in @MotoAmerica’s #KingoftheBaggers race at @RoadAmerica. 

@vanceandhines Harley-Davidson rider @hayden69gillim finished 3rd to complete a Harley podium sweep.

“I ride because I feel like not enough people take risks and they’re scared of things. I do it because I love it. It’s like therapy.” - @mz.pietz

node.text: One of the longest running names in motorsports history, the Sportster has been in continuous production since 1957. Watch the full 2021 Sportster S reveal at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harley-Davidson on July 17, 2021 tagging @prideofgypsies. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Our history meets @prideofgypsies’s roots with the H-D X Momoa collection. This limited-edition, vintage-inspired collection features iconic designs and styling that tie back to H-D’s lineage while paying tribute to Jason Momoa’s Polynesian heritage. Every piece tells a different story, capturing the spirit of the open road. All-American made.

Everyone involved in the process of creating the Sportster S has an emotional connection to the bike. Today we hear from some of the folks who build it — the talented men and women at the Harley-Davidson Powertrain Operations in Menomonee Falls, WI. 

Watch the full 2021 Sportster S reveal at the link in our bio.

Watch the final episode of Battle of the Baggers: Season 2 and relive the full season at the link in our bio.
